    "tool": "update_issue",
    "input": {
      "assignees": [],
      "body": "First, my <3 for creating this website/lessons! I've been recommending it for years, especially for \"scientific computing\" users who often didn't even have a \"CS education\" but are now developing software and running in Unix environments.\r\n\r\nSSH is very unintuitive, so the explanation of keys, & port-forwarding is extremely valuable. I've added here a section on how to do \"SSH Proxying\" because that's another common use case. From their perspective \"my data is on host B behind SSH server A, and I want to download (upload) it\" is extremely common.\r\n\r\nHopefully this repo/class is still being loved and can be updated!\n\n---\n_This PR was originally from a fork: **nyetsche/missing-semester** (branch: `ssh-proxy`)_",
